.

#illustration #illustrator #oc

Been drawing this girl before I wrote her story. Art was always something I was confident in, but writing was a secret background passion. I waited so long to start because I didn’t feel “ready.” As if waiting will grant me more skill. Like I only had one story in me, and I would waste it if I didn’t do it “right.” I’m the process of editing my first novel right now with help from my roommates. I’m a big Stephen King reader. In his memoir he said something about first drafts. Something like “all they have to do is exist.” That was my motivation for a good chunk of the process.

#digitalartist #illustration #oc #bookillustration

I have a pretty chaotic process when painting. I usually don’t know what I want until a few hours in, and spend a lot of time playing with color before I decide on anything. I used to find The Process the worst part of making art. I just wanted it done. I wanted something to show. 

My feed right now is bombarded by AI art. Computers can compile all the existing knowledge masters have built for thousands of years. The algorithm wants fast content, and we as creators now have to compete with robots that can produce “art” in seconds. It’s like art-mageddon. The end times have come. I should feel threatened, right? AI can bypass The Process! 

But that’s what makes something art. The beautiful, messy unsureness of it. Erasing until the paper is raw. Realizing you have been painting on the wrong layer the entire time. Spilling your coffee on the canvas. Eyes tired. Brain tired. 

Art is communication. Is protest. Is love. Is reaching for divinity. Not “content.” AI can’t replace creativity.

Happy #petticoatwednesday! 

🪲🕷 🐛 🪳

Photoshoot with @tbbarnabee inspired by those weird dreams you confuse for childhood memories. It was cathartic to play with glitter glue and pipe cleaners, summoning demons like kids again. 🎱💫🦋

A few of my previous photo collabs with Tulula are already on my personal ig (@peyjuly) but all of them will also live on @rockpapermonsters. 

I’m trying to find ways to combine my art with my writing and my love of history, so I plan to post more like this. I used to put everything on this page, not just drawing, and I think I want to go back to that.
